Let $d\ge 3$ and $p>0$. Let $\|x\|_p$ denote the $\ell_p$ (quasi-)norm of a $d$-dimensional vector $x$. Holevo and Utkin \cite{HU26} conjectured that for $0<p\le 1$, \[ \min \left\{ rac{\|x\|_p}{\|x\|_2}:\vec{0}
eq x\in\mathbb R^d,\ \sum_{i=1}^d x_i=0ight\} =2^{1/p-1/2}; \] for $1<p<2$, \[ \min \left\{ rac{\|x\|_p}{\|x\|_2}:\vec{0}
eq x\in\mathbb R^d,\ \sum_{i=1}^d x_i=0ight\} = \min\left\{2^{1/p-1/2},\left( rac{(d-1)^{p/2}+(d-1)^{1-p/2}}{d^{p/2}}ight)^{1/p}ight\}; \] and for $2<q<\infty$ \[ \max\left\{ rac{\|x\|_q}{\|x\|_2}:\vec{0}
eq x\in\mathbb R^d,\ \sum_{i=1}^d x_i=0ight\} = \max\left\{2^{1/q-1/2},\left( rac{(d-1)^{q/2}+(d-1)^{1-q/2}}{d^{q/2}}ight)^{1/q}ight\}. \] They proved the $d=3$ case in \cite{HU26}. In this paper, we confirm the conjecture of the remaining cases $d\ge 4$.
